guiding the living ……, Father @wDN{Enlil}, shepherd of the black-headed, by his …… making the foreign countries bow low.

@(A.24 = 24-42) He whose …… strengthens the boundaries of heaven and earth, whose utterances unite them; lord whose ominous silence pervades the foreign lands, whose actions are spine-chilling, whose complex judgments cannot be revealed by anyone, whose knowledge is honoured by the foreign lands, whose strength is a great battle-net …… the foreign lands, a fine-mesh battle-net …… covering the disobedient; indefatigable …… in heaven, in possession of every one of the divine powers in their totality, linking together the ancient plans; south wind which covers the four quarters; @wDN{Enlil}, whose …… cannot be grasped, whose fame is enough to make people quake; @wDN{Enlil}, great in heaven, surpassing on earth, exceptional and wide-reaching in @wGN{Sumer}, @wDN{Nunamnir}, lord of princes, king of kings! He determined a good destiny in the holy city for me, @wRN{Išme-@wDN{Dagan}}, son of @wDN{Dagan}.

@(A.43 = 43-52) He named me with a favourable name even when my seed was inserted into the womb. @wDN{Nintur} stood by at my birth, and she established the office of @fsux{en} for me ……, even when my umbilical cord was cut. @wDN{Enlil}, my principal deity, bestowed on me the shepherdship of @wGN{Sumer}, and assigned to me a tireless protective goddess, adding also therewith a correct stature.
