@(A.53 = 53-75) His splendour …… the mountains, and his roar reaches beyond heaven and earth. He selected me from my people, and announced me to the Land. @wDN{Enlil}, king of the gods, gave me lordship over the south and over the uplands. At @wDN{Nunamnir's} instigation, @wDN{An} spoke encouragingly to me, and placed crook and staff in my hands. @wDN{Uraš} nursed me on her holy knees. In the @wTN{Ki-ur}, the great place, @wDN{Ninlil} in her radiant heart determined as my destiny that I should sit on an exalted dais until distant days, to enjoy in favour the reign which is my lot; that I should delight @wDN{Enlil}, and that I should daily attend to the @wTN{E-kur}. @wDN{Enki}, the great lord of @wSN{Eridug}, confirmed for me the good and great crown, …… everything, and richly conferred on me seven wisdoms. @wDN{Suen}, the firstborn son of @wDN{Enlil}, …… for me a royal throne that gathers together the divine powers, established an excellent lordly dais, and made my crown shine brilliantly until distant days.

@(A.76 = 76-89) @wDN{Nuska}, @wDN{Enlil's} minister, placed the royal sceptre in my hand, revealed the powers of @wTN{E-kur} to me, established there for me an awe-inspiring podium, and ensured that @wDN{Enlil's} heart was in a joyful mood. @wDN{Ninurta}, @wDN{Enlil's} mighty warrior, approached @wDN{Nunamnir} in speech on my behalf and secured (?) the favourable words of @wDN{Enlil} and @wDN{Ninlil} for me. He has made my reign of kingship excellent, has made me great in lordship, and is indeed my helper. In @wTN{E-kur} he prays continually on my behalf, and is indeed the constable of my kingship. He, who with mighty weapons makes all the foreign countries bow low, has put great power …… into my right hand.

@(A.90 = 90-99) @wDN{Utu} put justice and reliable words in my mouth. To make judgments, to reach decisions, to lead the people aright, to excel in rectitude, to keep the righteous on the track and to destroy the wicked, so that each man should speak justice to his brother, should make obeisance to his father, should not speak contrary words to his elder sister, and should respect his mother; so that the weak should not be handed over to the strong, so that the feeble should ……; so that the strong should not do just what he pleases, and so that one man should not be assigned to another @noteref{through debt}; to destroy wickedness and violence, and to make righteousness flourish -- all this @wDN{Utu}, the son born to @wDN{Ningal}, made my apportioned share.

@(A.100 = 100-111) @wDN{Inana}, the lady of heaven and earth ……, chose me as her beloved spouse. She put attractiveness in my waist-belt (?), looking at me with her life-giving look, as she lifted her radiant forehead to me, to make me step onto the flowery bed. She has uttered her unalterable holy word for me to spend long, long days in the @fsux{ŋipar}, combining the priestly office of @fsux{en} with the kingship and caring unceasingly for @wTN{E-ana}, and for my neck to become thick like a wild bull's in @wSN{Unug} as my splendour covers @wSN{Kulaba}.

@(A.112 = 112-132) @wDN{Enki} and @wDN{Ninki}, @wDN{Enul} and @wDN{Ninul}, the @wDN{Anuna}, the lords who determine destiny there, the spirits of @wSN{Nibru}, and the protective goddesses of the @wTN{E-kur}, those who among the great gods determine destinies there, have uttered an unchangeable @q[great gods,others]{“So be it!”} On his most favourable day, @wDN{Enlil}, king of the foreign lands, chose me, @wRN{Išme-@wDN{Dagan}}, son of @wDN{Dagan}, by extispicy. He looked upon me joyfully in @wTN{E-kur}, and spoke well of me to @wGN{Sumer}. …… a favourable reign in @wSN{Nibru}. I, @wRN{Išme-@wDN{Dagan}} …… restored @wSN{Urim} ……. …… in splendour. @wDN{Enlil} has commanded the favourable …… of my throne, the promotion of concord in @wGN{Sumer} and @wGN{Akkad} in their power, and restoration (?) of the …… brick buildings; and that I should daily tend the @wTN{E-kur}, that I should unceasingly provide for @wSN{Nibru}, and that I should care after the @wTN{Ki-ur}, the great place.

@(A.133 = 133-159) I, @wRN{Išme-@wDN{Dagan}}, have bent my neck to the commands of Father @wDN{Enlil}; I have paid attention to the utterances of my master. I have established justice in @wGN{Sumer}; I have secured (?) @wSN{Nibru} like heaven itself. I have gathered together the divine powers of the @wTN{E-kur}, I have paid attention to its old ordinances, and I have restored its neglected rites. I, @wRN{Išme-@wDN{Dagan}}, have ……. @wDN{Enlil's} very precious divine powers. …… @wDN{Ninlil's} ……. …… the interior of @wTN{E-kur} …… good, …… its exterior. ……, when I venerate ……. …… @wDN{Enlil} and ……, its favourable spirits in the courtyard, and I introduced its favourable protective goddesses into the @wTN{E-kur}. I have presented marvellous food offerings to @wDN{Enlil}. In the …… of @wDN{Enlil}, established with bread, …… great regular offerings, I made numerous the fat bulls and fat sheep, ……, fish and birds, in the house of my master. I made them smell tasty in the great ovens. I contested ……. With …… I doubled (?) the regular offerings. Like water I poured out …… and liquor in unadulterated strength, from the offerings storeroom, like the rainwater that is released from heaven.

@(A.160 = 160-182) @wDN{An} brought @wDN{Ninkasi} along with him …… to its ……, and I libated delicious …… beer, mixed with aromatic cedar essence, over the brickwork of @wTN{E-kur}. Daily I made the @wTN{E-kur} like a harvest-place, and each month on its seventh and fifteenth days I made the temple festive. Both inside and outside the house, like ……, I spread the scent of …….
