laying …… oil, …… cream, ……, first-fruits of the gardens, dates, ……, on the table of @wDN{Enlil}, my master, ……. The main part of my food, …… drink, his favourite things ……. @wDN{Enlil} ……. I am the …… son of @wDN{Enlil}, I am the …… of @wDN{Ninlil}, I am the strong young man of the @wTN{E-kur}. I am the foremost, with respectful strength, making excellent food offerings. I am untiring, indefatigable. Daily I shall issue instructions for what my master will have to eat, and what I will give to drink, fulfilling the great commands of @wTN{E-kur}: thereby I carry out correctly the instructions of my master @wDN{Enlil}.

@(A.183 = 183-195) I bring great gladness to the city whose interior and exterior are as blue-green as the sky, @wSN{Nibru}, the mooring pole of heaven and earth. I have exempted its labourers from carrying earth in baskets, and I have freed its troops from fighting. I have released its gold, silver, cattle and sheep, the tribute of the citizens of @wSN{Nibru}. As for the temple of @wDN{Enlil} my master, for @wDN{Ninlil}, and for @wDN{Ninurta}, the mighty hero of @wDN{Enlil}, I have exempted their labourers from service. Filtered beer (?), barley, oil and sheep's wool have been made a tithe. I …… @wGN{Sumer} and @wGN{Akkad}. I …… wickedness and violence, and established justice in @wGN{Sumer} and @wGN{Akkad}. I am the shepherd who loves justice. I am born of @wGN{Sumer}, a son of @wSN{Nibru}.

@(A.196 = 196-199) I am one who is always for ……. I am wise-eyed, of refined intelligence. I am full of advice, energetic in ……. I am all-knowing, singled out from the people.

